whare
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:1.a small house used by pioneer farmers as a home, boundary hut or out-station (fern-tree, manuka, nikau, ponga, slab, sod etc.) or a small hut for the single man on a farm or station (occasionally portable). 2.  a communal living quarters or bunkhouse for single men on a station, occ. latterly where each man has his own bedroom or whare in an adjoining row.
Origin:Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: see also stinkie, brownie
